<br>
First off (you all probably know this already), when you perform a style, the bonus that you get is a percentage of your base weapon damage.  Critical Strike bonuses tend to be pretty high, things like +400% damage for some of them.  Base damage can vary a lot, depending on your weapon specialization and the mob's level compared to yours, but the bonus damage stays pretty consistent within a tight range (like +390% to +410%).<br>
<br>
So here's what happened.<br>
<br>
First of all, here's my base weapon damage on the 100+ Garrote's I got in:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/asb1.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
There's nothing very consistent since we were killing everything from greens to oranges; also, my weapon skill is a touch less than 1/3 of my level, so that doesn't help.  Right around attack #100, when I got the attack speed buff, you'll notice a bit of a drop in my base weapon damage.  Hard to tell if it's very significant with my poor weapon specialization - it might just be a fluke.<br>
<br>
When you look at my bonus damage for those same attacks though - and this is the percentage damage added, so it's independent of base damage variance - it's not very pretty:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/asb3.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
My bonus damage for Garrote was nicely consistent, hovering around the +165% to +170% range, until I get the attack speed buff.  Then it drops to the +150%-+160% range.<br>
<br>
For comparison, here's my base weapon damage during the same period of time for my 80+ Achilles Heel attacks:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/asb2.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
And here's the percentage bonus for those same attacks:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/asb4.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
We have a problem.<br>
<br>
Attack speed buffs are lowering our bonus damage by huge amounts.  It looks like, but I can't verify, buffing our attack speed by a certain percentage reduces our style bonuses by an equal percentage.<br>
<br>
However, if increasing our attack speed like this also reduces our base weapon damage - which I've heard but don't have the specs to test - then we're paying for the buff twice.  It increases our attack speed, sure, but it lowers our base damage, then it also lowers our bonus percentage.  A 10% increase in our attack speed would lower our damage using styles by almost 15%.  A 40% increase in our attack speed would cut damage by over half.<br>
<br>
Can someone with a really high weapon spec verify the effects of attack speed increase on base weapon damage?<br>
<br>
Also, if bonuses to Quickness have the same effect, there's an even bigger problem.  Rogue damage is actually going to scale <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> down</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as we level, increase our stats, and get better buffs.  Other people have mentioned this problem, but I haven't seen any documentation on it.<br>
<br>
Either way... this just doesn't seem right. <p><b>Ciardha Sidhe</b><br><small>Elven Nightshade in the service of the Seelie Court</small><br>Guinevere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uditherdaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dither DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 11:02:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1627.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/dither/smiley2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attack Speed Buff... bad news.</span><hr size=1> Sabreur did a small quickness test i think, and found that even though our damage over time was decreased slightly, the higher quickness still paid off.  I'll try to find the post. <p>Dither Disgustipated<BR>
Kobold Shadowblade<BR>
Ragnarok, Palomides</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uditherdaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dither DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 11:05:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1627.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/dither/smiley2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attack Speed Buff... bad news.</span><hr size=1> One other thing to try and encompass in your test is the ammount of endurance used.  If an attack speed buff essentially adjusts your weapon speed, and endurance used relates to weapon speed, then it may all even out. <p>Dither Disgustipated<BR>
