Ragnarok, Palomides</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaiyasamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maiya Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 11:42:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1627.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attack Speed Buff... bad news.</span><hr size=1> With my Warden, Friar, Berserker and Nightshade I have not noticed any reduction in endurance usage as my attack speed increases. The endurance usage seems constant. The bad thing is, the percentage amount of endurance used by a style seems to relate to the character's constitution. Characters with higher constitution visually appear to use less endurance on the same styles than characters with lower constitution.<br>
<br>
I'm particularly noticing this with my Melee Nightshade and her 55 constitution and my Balanced Nightshade and her 45 constitution.<br>
<br>
Just a stab in the dark, (teehee, pun!) I think there is a serious penalty for having any stat below 60.<br>
 <p><p style="font-size: 80%">-- Maya: Norse Berserker, Nimue</p>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/02 11:42:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1627.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cableone.net/truggiero/smxumcard.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attack Speed Buff... bad news.</span><hr size=1> But the question I have is if it does &quot;even out&quot; then why the hell even put haste in the game? Why waste all that time coding for something that is going to &quot;even out&quot; damage wise and only be beneficial in very limited circumstances(ie caster disrupts)?<br>
<br>
