-- <i>Nightshade Team Lead</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uciardhasidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ciardha Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/9/02 2:34:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1627.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/ciardha60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attack Speed Buff... bad news.</span><hr size=1> I made an error in presentation in my original post.  The bonus damage percentages are labeled poorly - if it says 180% bonus damage, that's really +80% damage for a total of 180% damage, not +180% damage for a total of 280% damage.<br>
<br>
The full log in all of its 443k gory detail is available at:  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/speedbuff.log">www.starseer.com/nightsha...edbuff.log</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> as long as i'm hitting more often (increase in percentage) is higher than my damage per hit is droping (again percentage) then we come out on top<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That's what I'm saying - it doesn't even out.  We lose more damage than we gain by speed.<br>
<br>
If raising attack speed by any means (speed buff, quickness boost) decreases a weapon's base damage, then there's your appropriate scaling.  The effectiveness of your style shouldn't go down just because you're doing it faster - if a style gives an extra 80% damage normally, it shouldn't only give 60% because someone buffed you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> One other thing to try and encompass in your test is the ammount of endurance used.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I don't have any consistent, numeric way to log endurance use.  It would make sense if higher constitution gave a larger pool of endurance, but again, hard to tell with no numbers.  I've heard style endurance cost is related to weapon weight, as well.<br>
<br>
For reference, I'm level 25, Critical Strike 25, Piercing 8.  I'll be raising my piercing in the future.  A lot.<br>
<br>
